Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
uiSet(25.10)                                                      uiSet(25.10)

Name
       uiSet - Sets the specified property of an element

Syntax
       uiSet

       [-help]

       <name>

       [-before <name>]

       [-checked {true | false}]

       [-command <string>]

       [-disabled {true | false}]

       [-enablevar <string>]

       [-foreground <string>]

       [-geometry <string >| -fullscreen {true | false}]

       [-icon <filename>]

       [-in <name>]

       [-label <string>]

       [-menuseparate {true | false}]

       [-message <string>]

       [-movable {true | false}]

       [-newline {true | false}]

       [-shortcut <string>]

       [-statusbar <string>]

       [-title <string>]

       [-tooltip <string>]

       [-underline <integer>]

       [-value <string >]

       [-variable <string>]

       [-visible {true | false}]

       [-visiblevar <string>]

       Sets  the  specified  property  of an element. Use this command to cus-
       tomize the Innovus graphical interface by configuring various interface
       elements, such as submenus and commands. The properties that can be set
       for a specific element depends on the type of that element. To see  the
       list  of  properties  that  can be set for each type, see the "Accepted
       Properties for Each Type" section below.

       For elements of type menu, submenu, command, check,  radio,  separator,
       toolbar,  and  toolbutton,  the uiSet command works like the tk command
       <widget>configure. For the main window (main), it  works  like  the  tk
       command wm.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each uiSet parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man uiSet

       <name> Specifies  the  name of the element whose property is to be set.
              An error is returned if specified <name> does not exist.

       -before <name>
              Sets the specified element  before  the  element  identified  by
              <name>.

       -checked {true | false}
              Checks or unchecks the specified element.

              Note:  You  can  use the -checked parameter only for elements of
              type check or radio.

       -command <string>
              Specifies the Tcl command to be executed when the specified ele-
              ment is invoked.

              Note: You can use the -command parameter only if you are  adding
              elements of type command, check, radio or toolbutton.

       -disabled {true | false}
              Disables or enables the specified interface element.

              Note:  You  can use the -disabled parameter only for elements of
              type menu, submenu, command, check, radio or toolbutton. The pa-
              rameter is NOT applicable for elements of type toolbar and sepa-
              rator.

       -enablevar <string>
              Sets the Tcl global variable for Enable status.

       -foreground <string>
              Specifies the foreground color of the icon of the specified  in-
              terface element.

              Note:  You  can  use  the  -foreground parameter only if you are
              adding an element of type toolbutton.

       -fullscreen {true | false}
              Maximizes the main window. This property can be set only for the
              element main.

              Note: This option cannot be used with -geometry.

       -geometry <string>
              Modifies the geometry of the specified window element.

       -icon <filename>
              Specifies the file name of the toolbutton icon.  <filename>  can
              be  the  full path of the icon file or an icon name supported by
              Innovus.

              The icon  names  used  in  Innovus  can  be  queried  using  the
              gui_get_ui command.

              For  list  of supported image formats for the icon file, see the
              "Supported Image Formats" section of the  Customizing  the  User
              Interface chapter in the User Guide.

              Note:  The  -icon  parameter  is applicable only for elements of
              type toolbutton.

       -in <name>
              Specifies the name of the parent element.

       -label <string>
              Specifies the label to be displayed on the element  being  modi-
              fied.

              Note: This parameter is NOT applicable for elements of type sep-
              arator.

       -menuseparate {true | false}
              Specifies  whether  or  not a menu or submenu can be torn off or
              detached.

              * When set to true (default), a dashed line appears at  the  top
                of the menu or submenu to indicate that it can be detached.

              * When  set  to  false, the dashed line no longer appears at the
                top of the menu or submenu and it cannot be detached.

              Note: This parameter is applicable for elements of type menu and
              submenu.

       -message <string>
              Specifies the message to be displayed on the element being modi-
              fied.

              Note: This parameter is applicable for elements of type  status-
              bar.

       -movable {true | false}
              Specifies  whether  or  not the element being modified should be
              movable.

              Note: The -movable parameter is applicable only for elements  of
              type toolbar.

       -newline {true | false}
              Specifies whether or not the element being modified should be on
              a new row.

              Note:  The -newline parameter is applicable only for elements of
              type toolbar.

       -shortcut <string>
              Specifies the shortcut key for a command, check box, radio  but-
              ton, or toolbutton.

              Note:  You can use the -shortcut parameter only if you are modi-
              fying elements of type command, check, radio, or toolbutton.

       -statusbar <string>
              Sets the statusbar of the specified window element.

       -title <string>
              Specifies the window title.

       -tooltip <string>
              Specifies the tooltip text for the toolbar or toolbutton you are
              adding.

              Note: The -tooltip parameter is applicable only for elements  of
              type toolbar and toolbutton.

       -underline <integer>
              Specifies the integer index of the character to be underlined in
              the  element  label.  The  index begins with 0 and should have a
              value less than or equal to the length of the element label. For
              instance, if you want the second letter of the element label  to
              appear underlined, specify <integer>as 1.

              Note: The -underline parameter is NOT applicable for elements of
              type toolbar, separator, and toolbutton.

       -value <stringValue>
              Specifies the value to be stored in the associated variable when
              the specified radio button is selected.

              Note:  The  -value  parameter is applicable only for elements of
              type radio.

       -variable <string>
              When modifying a check box or radio button,  specifies  the  Tcl
              global variable for the item.

       -visible {true | false}
              Specifies the visibility status of the element being modified.

       -visiblevar <string>
              Sets the Tcl global variable for Visible status.

Accepted Properties for a Specific Type
              * For  the  main  window (main), the following properties can be
                set:

                -geometry {<width>x<height> | <width>x<height>+<x>+<y>}

                 -title <title>

                -visible true | false

              * For a status bar (statusbar), the following  property  can  be
                set:

                -enablevar <string>

                 -in <parentname>

                -message <msg>

                 -visible true | false

                 -visiblevar <string>

              * For elements of type menu or submenu, the following properties
                can be set:

                -enablevar <string>

                 -before <nextSiblingName>]

                 -disabled true | false

                 -in <parentName>

                 -label <label> -menuseparate true | false

                -underline <index>

                 -visible true | false

                 -visiblevar <string>

              * For  elements of type command, radio, and check, the following
                properties can be set:

                -disabled true | false

                 -label <label>

                 -underline <index>

                 -command <commandName>

                 -in <parentName>

                 -before <nextSiblingName>

                 -enablevar <string>

                 -visible true | false

                 -visiblevar <string>

                 -shortcut <string>

                For radio and check, the -checked and -variable properties can
                also be set.

              * For elements of type toolbutton, the following properties  can
                be set:

                -state normal | disabled

                 -label <label>

                 -tooltip <toolTipText>

                 -underline <index>

                 -foreground <colorName>

                 -icon <iconName>

                 -command <commandName>

                 -in <parentName>

                 -before <nextSiblingName>

                 -enablevar <string>

                 -visible true | false

                 -visiblevar <string>

                 -shortcut <string>

Examples
              * The  following command changes the label of the Verify menu in
                the main window to NewVerify:

                uiSet verify -label NewVerify

              * The following command maximizes the Innovus main window:

                uiSet main -fullscreen

              * The following command makes the View menu in the  main  window
                non-detachable:

                uiSet view -menuseparate false

